Author: gibsonf1
Content: I designed an office for Crabel Capital in Milwaukee - a whole floor mainly for the programmers.  We started with prefabricated modular movable walls, but they ended up costing 4x + more than framed walls with gyp board.  We ended up using framed walls.  (The tax advantage couldn't come close to closing that big of a gap.)

Author: whacked_new
Content:
Great reasoning. Here's a quote from the Joel discussion board.

http://discuss.joelonsoftware.com/default.asp?biz.5.470472.11\n"This is from a P.R. pro. Monday is the day that most announcements go out. You still want it to be early in the week but to avoid the crowd, it makes sense to do it on Tuesday."

The odd thing is everybody followed this advice it wouldn't work. So the sluggish Monday idea is pretty compelling :)
